20/04/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Romanian Economy Minister Dan Ioan Popescu arrived in Ankara on Monday (19 April) to attend meetings of the Turkey-Romania Joint Economic Commission.
The meetings will focus on ways to boost bilateral economic co-operation and to encourage investments.
Also Monday, Turkey signed an environmental protection co-operation agreement with Bulgaria.
Reducing pollution levels in the Black Sea region is a key aim of the deal.
(Anadolu Agency, Rompres, ANA, Turkish Daily News, BTA - 19/04/04)
